{"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/2255", "repo": "rails", "body": "I share the concerns of @josevalim. Just because it's currently slow doesn't mean that we should resign ourselves to it always being slow.\r\n\r\nI agree the code is too complex, but I wonder if it could instead be refactored into a helper class that would build the class-eval'ed string.\r\n\r\n(Incidentally, before I went away last week I was working on a speed improvement for delegate that gets rid of the __send__ call in most cases, but it's complicated because it needs to handle edge cases and it requires deprecating the use of delegate on non-public methods. [It's not done yet...])", "_id": {"$oid": "523845d4bd3543c151010e60"}, "issue_id": 2255, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/1654323", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/2255#issuecomment-1654323", "updated_at": "2011-07-26T14:11:13Z", "user": {"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/subscriptions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/events{/privacy}", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/repos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/gists{/gist_id}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton", "login": "jonleighton", "gravatar_id": "2940bc7d4506f3e099e3dcc32a412b98", "html_url": "https://github.com/jonleighton", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/following{/other_user}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/received_events", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/orgs", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/2940bc7d4506f3e099e3dcc32a412b98?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F798cebccb32617ad94123450fd137104.png", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "id": 1979, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/followers", "type": "User"}, "created